(24, 1, '2021-06-17 09:38:11', '2021-06-17 09:38:11', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Google Street View will soon be available inside more than 100 train stations across Sydney, making trip planning easier.A year-long project mapping 143 train and metro stations across the city mean that commuters can access information about travel before leaving the house.The information about where platforms, entries, and exits are located will make stations much more accessible for people in wheelchairs, or with prams or luggage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Stations, in general, are places where people are on the way to somewhere, they may be under time pressure, they want to make that train or that bus,\" director of product management at Google Australia, Ramesh Nagarajan, said.\"It helps people plan ahead of time - get a feeling of what the station will be like, how complicated it will be.\"The stations were mapped using backpacks with 15 cameras mounted on them, arranged so a 360 panoramic shot could be taken.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><img alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Transport for NSW also gave Google every little detail about each station which has helped the tech giant improve their navigation instructions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I think this is one of the coolest things to hit the train network in years,\" NSW Transport Minister Andrew Constance said.\"It just gives everyone a greater sense of mobility when moving in and out of the network.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Google Street View is now available inside more than 100 train stations', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'google-street-view-is-now-available-inside-more-than-100-train-stations', '', '', '2021-06-17 09:38:53', '2021-06-17 09:38:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-blog/?p=24', 0, 'post', '', 0),
