(35, 1, '2021-06-17 09:44:43', '2021-06-17 09:44:43', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>(AP) —&nbsp;</strong>The Brooklyn Nets will continue to play without Kyrie Irving and don’t know exactly what kind of production they will get from James Harden as the star players deal with injuries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>None of that might make any difference if Kevin Durant keeps performing the way he has thus far in Brooklyn’s second-round playoff series with the Milwaukee Bucks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Nets own a 3-2 series lead thanks largely to Durant, who delivered a performance for the ages as Brooklyn rallied from a 17-point deficit in a&nbsp;<a class=\"\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/milwaukee-bucks-brooklyn-nets-nba-sports-83d375cf1846699201da87815d734f16\">114-108 Game 5 victory&nbsp;</a>Tuesday at Brooklyn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That leaves the Nets facing a dilemma as the series returns to Milwaukee for Game 6 on Thursday. After Durant played all 48 minutes and&nbsp;<a class=\"\" href=\"https://apnews.com/article/milwaukee-bucks-brooklyn-nets-nba-sports-cb2b11beaefa9470277980fdc28c5b9f\">Harden played 46 minutes Tuesday,</a>&nbsp;how long can they reasonably play in Game 6?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I think that’s something that we have to feel out as we go,” Nets coach Steve Nash said Wednesday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nash would rather not drain his veteran team this early in the postseason as the Nets chase their first NBA championship. With all the injuries involving star players across the league, Nash acknowledged he thinks “the championship this year will be decided on health as much as anything.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But he also wants to avoid a Game 7.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“There is no championship if you don’t get out of this series,” Nash said. “There’s obviously a point where you have to go and you have to play like we did last night. If it presents itself that we don’t have to overburden them, we’d be happy not to. But if we have to, we have to. That’s just the nature of it.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nash said both Durant and Harden felt fine after their heavy workloads Tuesday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Harden shot 1 of 10 and scored just five points but had eight assists and six rebounds in his first action since tightness in his right hamstring knocked him out in the opening minute of Game 1.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Irving missed all of Game 5 and won’t play Thursday after&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nba.com/news/kyrie-irving-exits-game-4-with-right-ankle-sprain\">spraining his right ankle in Game 4</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Durant picked up the slack Tuesday by collecting 49 points, 17 rebounds and 10 assists. He became the first player in NBA history to have at least 45 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists in a playoff game.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That continued an impressive postseason for Durant, who is averaging 33.6 points, 10.8 rebounds, 5.8 assists, 2 steals and 1.4 blocks in this series.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“He’s the best player in the world right now,” Bucks forward and two-time MVP Giannis Antetokounmpo said after Game 5.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Bucks wasted a golden opportunity to take control of the series when they couldn’t hang on to their big lead in Game 5. Now they find themselves in a must-win situation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“We’ve got to focus on ourselves and control what we can control,” Antetokounmpo said. “What we can control is our effort, and going into Game 6, hopefully we can bring it and put ourselves in position to win the game.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Related</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.nba.com/news/kevin-durant-etches-name-among-nbas-greatest-showings\">Durant etches name among NBA\'s greatest showingsFew playoff performers have ever reached the heights Kevin Durant achieved with his 49-point, triple-double masterpiece against the Bucks.</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.nba.com/news/nba-twitter-reacts-to-kevin-durants-legendary-performance\">NBA Twitter reacts to Durant\'s legendary Game 5Active and retired players alike lavished praise on Durant via Twitter following his epic Game 5 outing against the Bucks.</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.nba.com/news/what-just-happened-around-nba-keeping-track-of-busy-wednesday\">Keep track of what just happened around NBAThe coaching carousel and big injury information takes the spotlight on a busy news day in the NBA.</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.nba.com/news/reports-knee-injury-could-force-kawhi-leonard-to-miss-game-5\">Clippers: No timetable for Kawhi\'s returnKawhi Leonard appeared to injure his right knee in the closing minutes of Game 4 against the Jazz.</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'James Harden available, Kyrie Irving out for Nets as they try to advance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '34-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-06-17 09:44:43', '2021-06-17 09:44:43', '', 34, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-blog/?p=35', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(36, 1, '2021-06-17 09:46:36', '2021-06-17 09:46:36', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coca-Cola and Heineken are getting tackled on social media after two soccer stars visibly snubbed them at a tournament sponsored by both beverage makers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both Portuguese forward Cristiano Ronaldo and French midfielder Paul Pogba slid bottles from the sponsors away from themselves during separate press conferences.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On Monday, ahead of Portugal’s opening game at the Euro 2020 tournament against Hungary, in Budapest, the health-conscious Ronaldo was caught on camera as he moved the soft drinks away from him. He then held up a bottle of water and said, “Agua.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Later, Pogba, a Muslim, removed a bottle of Heineken beer from him during a press conference.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Headlines and social media conversation noted that Coca-Cola’s share price fell Monday and attributed it to the global soccer star’s actions. But in fact, there was no real indication that the actions had affected the stock price.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coca-Cola’s share price immediately fell at the stock market opening at 9:30 a.m. ET from $56.08 to $55.25 even before Ronaldo’s press conference was scheduled to begin at 9:45, just 4 cents above the day’s low.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The stock inched up slightly during the conference following the gesture, increasing to $55.30.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Clips of both incidents shot around social media, drawing some praise for the soccer stars’ gestures.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ronaldo was “setting a positive example for young fans and showing his disdain for a cynical marketing attempt to link him with a sugary drink,” Britain’s Obesity Health Alliance tweeted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Recommended</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/science/science-news/lab-leak-theory-science-scientists-rcna1191?icid=recommended\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><a class=\"\" href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/health/coronavirus\">CORONAVIRUS</a><a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/science/science-news/lab-leak-theory-science-scientists-rcna1191?icid=recommended\">There\'s still no evidence of a Chinese lab leak. But here’s what\'s changed, scientists say.</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/outrage-pandemic-racism-may-boost-asian-american-voter-turnout-nyc-rcna1201?icid=recommended\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><a class=\"\" href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/asian-america\">ASIAN AMERICA</a><a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/outrage-pandemic-racism-may-boost-asian-american-voter-turnout-nyc-rcna1201?icid=recommended\">Outrage over pandemic racism may boost Asian American voter turnout in NYC</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coca-Cola responded to a request for comment by pointing NBC News to a statement from European soccer\'s governing body, UEFA, which said the company offered \"a range of drinks to suit different tastes and needs, which are available to players throughout the tournament.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It added that players \"can choose their preferred beverage\" at press conferences.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A spokesperson for Heineken, an official sponsor of the tournament, said in an email, \"We fully respect everyone\'s decision when it comes to their beverage of choice.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the richest athletes on the planet, Ronaldo has a lucrative brand off the pitch, commanding huge endorsement deals, and with 299 million followers, he is the most-followed athlete on Instagram — even surpassing reality TV star Kim Kardashian West and singers Ariana Grande and Beyoncé.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Earlier this month, Ronaldo tweeted: “My body is my weapon. It’s the most important thing to me. In football, we are always told to eat well and train well to have a longer professional career.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 2006, Ronaldo appeared in a commercial for Coca-Cola and was featured in a commercial for fast-food giant KFC.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coca-Cola owns over 500 beverage brands globally, including soft drinks, energy drinks, sports drinks, and bottled water.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ronaldo\'s action won praise from sports commentators on social media, as well as Tampa Bay Buccaneers quarterback&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/TomBrady/status/1404572271973388290\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tom Brady</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Beverage makers mocked after soccer stars Ronaldo and Pogba snub drinks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beverage-makers-mocked-after-soccer-stars-ronaldo-and-pogba-snub-drinks', '', '', '2021-06-17 09:46:36', '2021-06-17 09:46:36', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-blog/?p=36', 0, 'post', '', 0),
