(40, 1, '2021-06-17 09:48:16', '2021-06-17 09:48:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After 16 seasons, 671 games, 101 goals, five league titles and four European Cups, Sergio Ramos is leaving&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/football/realmadrid\">Real Madrid</a>. The club’s captain will say his final goodbye on Thursday, 13 days before his contract formally runs out.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"linkDestination\":\"custom\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\" id=\"db5682b9-d383-40d9-befa-71c27aba34ab\"><a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/may/24/spain-leave-sergio-ramos-out-of-euro-2020-squad-and-call-up-aymeric-laporte\"><img src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/da1a5406aadb2c3f57ef1dbf2de63ccc869834a2/0_65_2890_1732/master/2890.jpg?width=460&amp;quality=85&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=max&amp;s=03f8b822e05c43fb86747037549d6cc8\" alt=\"\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unable to reach an agreement with the club president, Florentino Pérez, to continue, Ramos becomes a free agent on 1 July. Although he is 35, he has no intention of retiring and the centre-back’s final destination is still not finalised, with reports linking him to a catalogue of clubs including Paris Saint-Germain, Manchester City and Sevilla.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although the news came as no real surprise after months in which negotiations over a new deal had come to a halt and, with Ramos’s relationship with Pérez a difficult one all too often played out in the press, Madrid’s announcement on Wednesday evening still had a huge impact.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In May 2019, Ramos had said that he “would play for Madrid for free” but he had wanted a new two-year deal on the same €15m salary, minus a 10% reduction applied across the squad because of the coronavirus crisis. Real would offer only a single year, and recently signed David Alaba on a free transfer from Bayern Munich. One last round of talks between Ramos and Pérez this week failed to break the deadlock, if indeed there was ever rally any intention of doing so.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Real Madrid confirm Sergio Ramos will leave after 16 years at club', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'real-madrid-confirm-sergio-ramos-will-leave-after-16-years-at-club', '', '', '2021-06-17 09:48:16', '2021-06-17 09:48:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wp-blog/?p=40', 0, 'post', '', 0),
